Changelog
All notable changes to the Network & Vulnerability Scanner, compiled from v1.0 to present.

v2.2
ADDED — Ghost‑in‑the‑Shell intro animation: On the first user gesture, a typewriter sequence prints to #terminalOutput with randomized timing, newline pauses, and per‑character sounds. Includes a live timestamp and scanner header block. Override via init({ intro: { text: '...' } }).

ADDED — newlinePauseMs option in typeOut(): Configurable extra delay after each \n. Defaults to 0 normally, 160ms in the intro.

ADDED — onComplete callback in typeOut(): Runs when the animation finishes and auto‑focuses #cmdInput.

ADDED — Live timestamp in default intro text: Generated at unlock time so it reflects the user's first interaction.

IMPROVED — AudioContext unlock fix: Now created inside the gesture handler (unlock()), not at init(), ensuring browsers resume it correctly.

IMPROVED — Two‑phase buffer loading: WAV files fetched as ArrayBuffer at init; decodeAudioData() deferred until unlock. .slice(0) prevents detachment bugs.

IMPROVED — Unlock listeners moved to window: Ensures broadest gesture capture. Sibling listeners removed manually with { once: true }.

IMPROVED — playBuffer() guard: Checks audioCtx.state === 'running' before source.start() to avoid silent errors.

IMPROVED — typeOut() uses observerPaused flag instead of disconnecting the MutationObserver.

CHANGED — Intro text defaults to null: Timestamp built at runtime using nowTimestamp().

v2.1
ADDED — Terminal sound effects (terminal_sfx.js): Adds typewriter audio to the Flask GUI. Loaded from /static/terminal_sfx.js.

ADDED — Web Audio API integration: Shared suspended AudioContext resumed only on real user gesture.

ADDED — Multi‑sample click engine: Randomly selects from click1.wav–click4.wav. Dedicated sounds for enter.wav, backspace.wav, and optional error.wav.

ADDED — Per‑play audio jitter: Randomized volume (±15%) and playback rate (±3%) for organic sound.

ADDED — Throttling and rate limiting: 20ms cooldown and 30‑sounds‑per‑second cap. Bulk appends collapse to one sound.

ADDED — Input typing hooks: Keydown listener on #cmdInput plays appropriate sound per key.

ADDED — Output observer mode: MutationObserver on #terminalOutput plays sounds for SSE output.

ADDED — TerminalSFX.typeOut(text, opts): Character‑by‑character output with sound. Observer paused during playback.

ADDED — Public API on window.TerminalSFX: init, unlock, typeOut, playClick.

ADDED — Top‑level config object: All selectors, paths, jitter, cooldowns, thresholds, and flags in DEFAULT_CONFIG.

ADDED — Sound file structure: /static/sfx/ directory with required click samples and optional error sound.

v2.0
ADDED — Browser‑based GUI (app.py): Flask server at http://127.0.0.1:5000 providing an interactive terminal interface.

ADDED — Live streaming output via SSE: Results stream line‑by‑line in real time.

ADDED — Live elapsed timer: Status bar counts up during active scans.

ADDED — Color‑coded CLI output: Cyan for phases, green for open ports, yellow for warnings, red for vulnerabilities.

ADDED — Structured section headers and dividers: Clear sections for port scan, host info, and vulnerability scan.

IMPROVED — OS match formatting: Clean numbered list of top three OS matches instead of raw dict.

IMPROVED — Banner grabbing flow: Banners collected silently and displayed in a formatted table.

IMPROVED — Vulnerability description truncation: Capped at 120 characters with ellipsis.

IMPROVED — Scan duration display: Microseconds removed.

CHANGED — Project structure: Two entry points (scanner.py for CLI, app.py for GUI).

CHANGED — Dependencies: Added flask; removed unused requests.

CHANGED — Documentation example output: Updated to reflect new structured format.

REMOVED — Inline progress noise: Phase progress now shown only in labeled headers.

REMOVED — Raw hostname and vulnerability dict dumps: Replaced with formatted output.

v1.0
Initial release. Single‑file CLI scanner (scanner.py) with port scanning, banner grabbing, and Nmap‑based OS and vulnerability detection. Raw dictionary output. No formatting.